
Overview of noun flint

The noun flint has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) flint -- (a hard kind of stone; a form of silica more opaque than chalcedony)
2. Flint, Flint River -- (a river in western Georgia that flows generally south to join the Chattahoochee River at the Florida border where they form the Apalachicola River)
3. Flint -- (a city in southeast central Michigan near Detroit; automobile manufacturing)

Overview of adj flint

